            <span id="ChapterParagraphOne">
            <span id="BigFirstLetterText">M</span>y parents’ spirituality: it's interesting, I must say. My dad struggled all of his life. I'm sure he must have been very spiritual when he was a kid, but when he was having us—when reality set in—he didn't feel like there was a God. The only time he had a stable income was the five years after he got married, and then when I was born he lost his job. Ever since that time, life was very rocky for him. For him to believe there was a God was very difficult, if not impossible. He still believed there was a deity, he still believed there were spirits. He would use spiritual stories to impress us about life. He impressed on us that you need to do good in order to have good things happen to you. .<br />
            </span>

