            <span id="BigFirstLetterText">M</span>y father’s religious beliefs were very free, in that he didn’t force his beliefs upon others. When I was a teenager, I joined the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints. He said, “If you like it, then go.” He never said I couldn’t go. My mother was the same way, very democratic, never forcing her beliefs on anyone else either. Although they never really went to church, I would accompany my mother to Catholic services when I was young. <br />
